   "body" : "This fixes an edge case (introduced by #6654 and reported by @sipa here: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/6654#issuecomment-142345556) in removing an entry from the mempool during the middle of a reorg, where the entry has an in-block ancestor which has not yet had its descendant state updated for the transaction being removed.\r\n\r\nThe first commit updates the ```mempool_packages.py``` rpc-test to include a test that demonstrates the bug; the second commit provides a fix.\r\n",
